    <figure id="fig-ch17_00_01" class="splash"><media id="fs-idm30250080" alt="Photo A shows an injection needle and small glass vial labeled 100 doses Smallpox vaccine, dead calf lymph type. Photo B is a transmission electron micrograph of the smallpox virus. It has an oval shape, with a dumbbell-shaped viral core inside, which contains the viral DNA.">
